<article>
    <h1>Fac&#xAD;tor of home stu&#xAD;dios</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201220/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-20"><time>2020-12-20</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline">Chan&#xAD;tal Sa&#xAD;jan</span>
    </section>

    <p>XOp­ti­mal light­ing, clear au­dio qual­ity and neu­tral back­drops. In the year of work­ing from home, work­ers had to mas­ter the art of video con­fer­enc­ing as it re­placed phys­i­cal meet­ings.</p>
    <p>To l ook their best for th­ese vir­tual meet­ings, some have in­vested in stag­ing media para­pher­na­lia.</p>
    <p>At pho­tog­ra­phy and elec­tron­ics shops, for in­stance, you can get ring lights ($30 to $200) to add a glow to the face. They are usu­ally paired with cir­cu­lar re­flec­tors ($40 to $150) that dif­fuse light to pre­vent heavy shad­ows from form­ing around the eyes and jaw­lines.</p>
    <p>For those who do not have time for elab­o­rate set-ups ahead of a meet­ing, us­ing or­di­nary desk lamps can achieve al­most the same ef­fect as a ring light and dif­fuser.</p>
    <p>Mr Benny Loh, 40, founder of video-pro­duc­tion house Food & Shel­ter, rec­om­mends us­ing one or two lamps.</p>
    <p>“Po­si­tion harsh lamps to face the wall near your com­puter or smart­phone screen for that re­flected light ef­fect,” he says. “Also, make sure the back­ground is not too bright, as it will be harder for oth­ers to fo­cus on your face.”</p>
    <p>Other gad­gets that are pop­u­lar for video meet­ings in­clude news­caster-style clip-on mi­cro­phones for crisp, clear au­dio qual­ity dur­ing video ses­sions.</p>
    <p>Mr Lester Yat, 38, a prod­uct spe­cial­ist at pho­to­graphic and video equip­ment re­tailer Alan Photo, says a top seller is the Au­dio-Tech­nica om­ni­di­rec­tional con­denser mi­cro­phones, which re­tail from $48 to $159 at its Sim Lim Square flag­ship and Fu­nan mall stores.</p>
    <p>“Th­ese are af­ford­able and do not dis­tort sound and can eas­ily be clipped onto cloth­ing while be­ing con­nected to a mo­bile phone or lap­top,” he says.</p>
    <p>Of course, no ap­pa­ra­tus will help you look more pro­fes­sional if you do not pay at­ten­tion to your ap­pear­ance. Re­mem­ber to dress prop­erly, comb your bed hair and main­tain good pos­ture too.</p>

